# SubPlots
# Dans le mme ordre que les coordones gomtre (obligatoire pour la reprojection)
SubPlots <- SubPlots %>% mutate(x = case_when(
  ID == "B.13" | ID == "B.14" | ID == "B.6" | ID == "B.5" ~ 200,
  ID == "B.12" | ID == "B.15" | ID == "B.7" | ID == "B.4" ~ 300,
  ID == "B.11" | ID == "B.16" | ID == "B.8" | ID == "B.3" ~ 400,
  ID == "B.10"| ID == "B.9" | ID == "B.1" | ID == "B.2" ~ 500)
) %>%
  mutate(y = case_when(
    ID == "B.13" | ID == "B.12" | ID == "B.11" | ID == "B.10" ~ 0,
    ID == "B.14" | ID == "B.15" | ID == "B.16" | ID == "B.9" ~ 100,
    ID == "B.6" | ID == "B.7" | ID == "B.8" | ID == "B.1" ~ 200,
    ID == "B.5"| ID == "B.4" | ID == "B.3" | ID == "B.2" ~ 300)
  )

subplots_corn <- SubPlots %>%
  left_join(subplots_corn, by = c("x", "y")) %>%
  select(X, Y, x, y, SubPlot, ID)

subplots_cornsf <- subplots_corn %>% 
  select(-SubPlot) %>% unique() %>%
  st_as_sf(coords = c('X','Y')) %>% 
  st_set_crs(crs(P16shp))

ALT <- ALT %>% 
  mutate(SubPlot = case_when(
    (x >= 200 & x < 300 & y >= 0 & y < 100) ~ 23,
    x >= 300 & x < 400 & y >= 0 & y < 100 ~ 24,
    x >= 400 & x <= 500 & y >= 0 & y < 100 ~ 25,
    x >= 200 & x < 300 & y >= 100 & y < 200 ~ 18,
    x >= 300 & x < 400 & y >= 100 & y < 200 ~ 19,
    x >= 400 & x <= 500 & y >= 100 & y < 200 ~ 20,
    x >= 200 & x < 300 & y >= 200 & y <= 300 ~ 13,
    x >= 300 & x < 400 & y >= 200 & y <= 300 ~ 14,
    x >= 400 & x <= 500 & y >= 200 & y <= 300 ~ 15) 
  ) %>% 
  
  # Quadrats (a m'a pris 2 jours...)
  mutate(X1 = substr(sprintf('%02d', x %% 100), 1,1)) %>% 
  mutate(Y1 = substr(sprintf('%02d', y %% 100), 1,1)) %>% 
  rowwise() %>% 
  mutate(X2 = as.character(((max((as.numeric(X1) -1), 0))))) %>% 
  mutate(Y2 = as.character(max((as.numeric(Y1) -1), 0))) %>% 
  
  mutate(X3 = as.character(max((as.numeric(X1) -1), 0))) %>% 
  mutate(Y3 = Y1) %>% 
  
  mutate(X4 = X1) %>% 
  mutate(Y4 =  as.character(max((as.numeric(Y1) -1), 0))) %>% 
  
  mutate(X2 = ifelse(X1== "0" & y!=0 & x!=200, "9", X2)) %>%
  
  mutate(Y2 = ifelse(Y1== "0"& y!=0 & x!=200, "9", Y2)) %>%
  
  mutate(X3 = ifelse(X1== "0", "9", X3)) %>%
  
  mutate(Y4 = ifelse(Y1== "0", "9", Y4)) %>%
  
  unite(col = "Quadrat1", c("X1", "Y1"),
        sep = "_", na.rm = TRUE, remove = F) %>%
  unite(col = "Quadrat2", c("X2", "Y2"),
        sep = "_", na.rm = TRUE, remove = F) %>%
  unite(col = "Quadrat3", c("X3", "Y3"),
        sep = "_", na.rm = TRUE, remove = F) %>%
  unite(col = "Quadrat4", c("X4", "Y4"),
        sep = "_", na.rm = TRUE, remove = F) %>% 
  pivot_longer(cols = starts_with("Quadrat"),
               names_to = "Quadrat_nb",
               values_to = "Quadrat") %>% 
  
  mutate(SubPlot = ifelse(Y1== "0" &
                            data.table::tstrsplit(Quadrat, split = "_")[[2]] != "0" & y!=0 & y!=300,
                          SubPlot+5, SubPlot)) %>%
  mutate(SubPlot = ifelse(X1== "0" & !SubPlot %in% c(13,18,23) &
                            data.table::tstrsplit(Quadrat, split = "_")[[1]] == "9" & x!=200 & x!=500,
                          SubPlot-1, SubPlot)) %>%
  
  filter(!((x== 200 | y == 0) & data.table::tstrsplit(Quadrat, split = "_")[[2]] == "9" &
             data.table::tstrsplit(Quadrat, split = "_")[[1]] == "9")) %>%
  filter(!((x==500 | y == 0) & data.table::tstrsplit(Quadrat, split = "_")[[2]] == "9" &
             data.table::tstrsplit(Quadrat, split = "_")[[1]] != "9")) %>%
  filter(!((y==300 | x== 200) & data.table::tstrsplit(Quadrat, split = "_")[[1]] == "9" &
             data.table::tstrsplit(Quadrat, split = "_")[[2]] != "9")) %>%
  filter(!(x==500 & data.table::tstrsplit(Quadrat, split = "_")[[1]] == "0")) %>% 
  filter(!(y==300 & data.table::tstrsplit(Quadrat, split = "_")[[2]] == "0")) %>% 
  select(X, Y, x, y, SubPlot, Quadrat) %>% unique() %>% 
  arrange(x)

Reprojection des piquets

Reprojette que pour 4 points de rfrence pas + pas - Les corners doivent etre dans le meme ordre dans le from et le to !

# install.packages("remotes")
# remotes::install_github('umr-amap/BIOMASS')
library(BIOMASS)
## Using temporary cache
##   It is recommended to use a permanent cache to avoid to re-download files on each session.
##   See function createCache() or BIOMASS.cache option.
?bilinear_interpolation
## dmarrage du serveur d'aide httpd ...
##  fini
projQuadrat <- data.frame() ; projQuadratS <- data.frame() ; projQuadratQ <- data.frame()

for(S in unique(Understory$Subplot)){
  # S = 18
  for(Q in unique(Understory$Quadrat)){ # par quadrat
    projQuadratQ <- bilinear_interpolation(
      coord = ALT[ALT$SubPlot == S & ALT$Quadrat == Q, c("x","y")], # quadrats theoric relative coord
      from_corner_coord = subplots_corn[subplots_corn$SubPlot == S, c("x","y")],  # SubPlot corner theoric relative coord
      to_corner_coord = geometre_coord[geometre_coord$SubPlot == S,], # SubPlot corner UTM coord
      ordered_corner = T) %>% 
      mutate(SubPlot = S) %>% 
      mutate(Quadrat = Q)
    
    projQuadratS <- rbind(projQuadratS, projQuadratQ)
  }
  projQuadrat <- rbind(projQuadrat, projQuadratS)
  
}
# plot((st_as_sf(subplots_corn[subplots_corn$SubPlot == S,], coords = c('X','Y'))))
projQuadratsf <- st_as_sf(projQuadrat, coords = c('X','Y'))
projQuadratsf <- st_set_crs(projQuadratsf, crs(P16shp))


ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = ALTsf, col="grey", size = 0.8) + # points to reproject
  geom_sf(data = geometre_coordsf, col="red", size = 1.5) + # reference
  geom_sf(data = projQuadratsf, aes(col=as.factor(SubPlot)), size = 0.8) + # reprojection
  labs(col= "SubPlot") +
  theme_classic() +
  ggtitle("After warping")

# ggsave("Quadrats.png", path = "D:/Mes Donnees/PhD/Figures/inventory",

projQuadrat <- data.frame() ; projQuadratS <- data.frame()
projTrees <- data.frame()

# Reprojeter chaque quadrat dans son subplot
for(S in unique(Understory$Subplot)){ # par SubPlot
  # S = 13 ; Q= "6_2"
  for(Q in unique(Understory$Quadrat)){ # par quadrat
    projQuadratQ <- bilinear_interpolation(
      coord = ALT[ALT$SubPlot == S & ALT$Quadrat == Q, c("x","y")], # quadrats theoric relative coord
      from_corner_coord = subplots_corn[subplots_corn$SubPlot == S, c("x","y")],  # SubPlot corner theoric relative coord
      to_corner_coord = geometre_coord[geometre_coord$SubPlot == S,], # SubPlot corner UTM coord
      ordered_corner = T) %>% 
      mutate(SubPlot = S) %>% 
      mutate(Quadrat = Q)
    
    projQuadratS <- rbind(projQuadratS, projQuadratQ)
    # # }
    
    # Reprojeter chaque arbre dans son quadrat
    # for(Q in unique(Understory$Quadrat)){ # par quadrat
    projTreesS <- bilinear_interpolation(
      coord = Understory[Understory$Subplot == S & Understory$Quadrat == Q, c("Dist.X","Dist.Y")], # Trees quadrats relative coord 
      from_corner_coord = data.frame(x = c(0, 0,10, 10),
                                     y= c(0,10, 0, 10)),  # quadrats theoric relative coord
      # from_corner_coord = ALT[ALT$SubPlot == S & ALT$Quadrat == Q, c("x","y")],  # quadrats theoric relative coord
      to_corner_coord = projQuadratQ[, c("X","Y")], # quadrats UTM coord
      ordered_corner = F) %>% 
      mutate(SubPlot = S) %>% 
      mutate(Quadrat = Q)
    
    projTrees <- rbind(projTrees, projTreesS)
  }
  
  projQuadrat <- rbind(projQuadrat, projQuadratS)
}
projQuadratsf <- st_as_sf(projQuadrat, coords = c('X','Y'))
projQuadratsf <- st_set_crs(projQuadratsf, crs(P16shp))

projTreessf <- st_as_sf(projTrees, coords = c('X','Y'))
